<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 01:50:52 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>一对父女伪造了沃霍尔、班克斯、毕加索等人的 200 多件艺术品，并以 200 万美元的价格出售</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-father-and-daughter-forged-more-than-200-artworks-by-warhol-banksy-picasso-and-others-and-old-them-for-2-million-180988641/</link><description>新泽西州居民委托波兰的一位艺术家制作这些赝品，他们将面临最高 20 年的监禁。他们因伪造美洲原住民艺术家的画作而受到特别处罚</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 21:26:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-father-and-daughter-forged-more-than-200-artworks-by-warhol-banksy-picasso-and-others-and-old-them-for-2-million-180988641/</guid></item><item><title>科学家们绘制了小鼠鼻子中第一张详细的气味传感器“气味图”，并嗅出了一些惊喜</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-create-the-first-detailed-smell-map-of-odor-sensors-in-the-mouse-nose-and-sniff-out-some-surprises-180988639/</link><description>在两项新研究中，研究人员利用遗传技术推翻了长期以来的假设，即带有气味探测器的神经细胞是随机排列的。他们不知道人类鼻子中是否也存在相同的空间组织</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 20:59:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-create-the-first-detailed-smell-map-of-odor-sensors-in-the-mouse-nose-and-sniff-out-some-surprises-180988639/</guid></item><item><title>这些建筑物和桥梁是英格兰和威尔士最“濒危”的建筑和桥梁，它们告诉我们很多关于维多利亚时代生活的信息</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-buildings-and-bridges-are-the-most-endangered-in-england-and-wales-and-they-tell-us-a-lot-about-life-in-the-victorian-era-180988642/</link><description>大英帝国鼎盛时期遗留下来的建筑揭示了 1800 年代和 1900 年代初不断变化的经济、医疗和教育趋势。但由于年久失修，他们的遗产正面临风险</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 19:41:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-buildings-and-bridges-are-the-most-endangered-in-england-and-wales-and-they-tell-us-a-lot-about-life-in-the-victorian-era-180988642/</guid></item><item><title>FDA 批准首个耳聋基因疗法，旨在恢复患有罕见遗传性疾病的儿童的听力</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-fda-approves-the-first-ever-gene-therapy-for-deafness-which-aims-to-restore-hearing-in-kids-with-a-rare-inherited-condition-180988635/</link><description>该机构的决定是基于一项临床试验的结果，在该试验中，该治疗改善了 80% 儿科参与者的听力。然而，聋人社区倡导者对治愈听力损失的努力感到担忧</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 17:44:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-fda-approves-the-first-ever-gene-therapy-for-deafness-which-aims-to-restore-hearing-in-kids-with-a-rare-inherited-condition-180988635/</guid></item><item><title>一位浮潜生物学家在野外拍摄了第一张新孵化的加州大鲵的照片。这就是为什么这很重要</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-snorkeling-biologist-snapped-the-first-ever-photos-of-newly-hatched-california-giant-salamanders-in-the-wild-heres-why-thats-a-big-deal-180988619/</link><description>这一发现提供了关于一个鲜为人知的物种的另一个关键数据点，对于该物种来说，每一次观察都很重要</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 17:16:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-snorkeling-biologist-snapped-the-first-ever-photos-of-newly-hatched-california-giant-salamanders-in-the-wild-heres-why-thats-a-big-deal-180988619/</guid></item><item><title>这尊拥有 400 年历史的巨型星盘 — 由莫卧儿工匠大师制作并为皇室所有 — 在拍卖会上拍出了数百万美元的价格</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-giant-400-year-old-astrolabe-made-for-royalty-by-mughal-master-craftsmen-and-owned-by-royalty-fetched-millions-at-auction-180988638/</link><description>古希腊天文学家和早期伊斯兰科学家使用星盘作为机械计算机来计算时间、确定高度并通过星星导航</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 14:07:26 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-giant-400-year-old-astrolabe-made-for-royalty-by-mughal-master-craftsmen-and-owned-by-royalty-fetched-millions-at-auction-180988638/</guid></item><item><title>观看首部已知的苏门答腊猩猩穿越树顶人造野生动物桥的视频</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/watch-the-first-known-video-of-a-sumatran-orangutan-crossing-a-human-made-wildlife-bridge-in-the-treetops-180988637/</link><description>印度尼西亚的一条公共道路将森林分隔开，森林中栖息着约 350 只野生猩猩和其他动物。因此，自然资源保护主义者建造了几座树冠桥来防止栖息地破碎化</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/watch-the-first-known-video-of-a-sumatran-orangutan-crossing-a-human-made-wildlife-bridge-in-the-treetops-180988637/</guid></item><item><title>这位法国艺术家以有趣的超现实雕塑而闻名，其蜿蜒的镜子刚刚打破了拍卖记录</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/known-for-her-amusing-surreal-sculptures-this-french-artists-sinuous-set-of-mirrors-just-shattered-auction-records-180988632/</link><description>Claude Lalanne 为设计师 Yves Saint Laurent 设计了反光套装。专家表示，它的重要性仅次于凡尔赛宫著名的镜子</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 21:16:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/known-for-her-amusing-surreal-sculptures-this-french-artists-sinuous-set-of-mirrors-just-shattered-auction-records-180988632/</guid></item><item><title>温暖的水域通常被困在南大洋深处。现在，他们正在侵入南极洲，威胁其冰层</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/warm-waters-are-usually-trapped-deep-within-the-southern-ocean-now-theyre-encroaching-on-antarctica-threatening-its-ice-180988636/</link><description>两项基于潜水机器人数据的新研究表明，气候变化如何改变海洋运动，从而危及极地冰盖的稳定性</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 19:48:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/warm-waters-are-usually-trapped-deep-within-the-southern-ocean-now-theyre-encroaching-on-antarctica-threatening-its-ice-180988636/</guid></item><item><title>这些爱德华·蒙克的画作被尼古丁和可可粉染色，在巧克力工厂的自助餐厅里挂了一个世纪。现在，它们将首次公开展示</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/edvard-munchs-lesser-known-chocolate-factory-friezes-head-to-exhibition-in-norway-180988634/</link><description>《呐喊》三十年后，这位挪威艺术家为弗雷亚巧克力工厂描绘了日常生活场景。这些艺术品将于今年春天在奥斯陆的他的同名博物馆展出</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 18:23:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/edvard-munchs-lesser-known-chocolate-factory-friezes-head-to-exhibition-in-norway-180988634/</guid></item><item><title>亚历山大·考尔德 (Alexander Calder) 认为让抽象艺术动起来“会很有趣”。他令人着迷的手机改变了雕塑的定义</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/alexander-calder-thought-it-would-be-fun-to-set-abstract-art-in-motion-his-mesmerizing-mobiles-transformed-the-definition-of-sculpture-180988631/</link><description>巴黎路易威登基金会举办的新展览重点展示了这位雕塑家的 300 件开创性动态艺术作品、大型公共雕塑、油画、素描和钢丝肖像</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 16:24:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/alexander-calder-thought-it-would-be-fun-to-set-abstract-art-in-motion-his-mesmerizing-mobiles-transformed-the-definition-of-sculpture-180988631/</guid></item><item><title>担心你的房子闹鬼？这种怪异的感觉可能来自一个令人惊讶的简单来源</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/worried-your-house-is-haunted-the-spooky-sensation-might-arise-from-a-surprisingly-simple-source-180988622/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，来自建筑物内的电力、供暖和机械系统的次声（低于人类典型听力范围的噪音）会让人们感到烦躁并诱发压力反应</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 15:44:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/worried-your-house-is-haunted-the-spooky-sensation-might-arise-from-a-surprisingly-simple-source-180988622/</guid></item><item><title>大约三年前，科学家在海底发现了这个神秘的金色球体。现在，他们终于知道那是什么了</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-found-this-mysterious-golden-orb-on-the-seafloor-nearly-three-years-ago-now-they-finally-know-what-it-is-180988624/</link><description>经过漫长而曲折的测试，史密森尼国家自然历史博物馆和其他机构的研究人员确定，这个奇怪的斑点曾经将一只巨大的海葵附着在岩石上</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-found-this-mysterious-golden-orb-on-the-seafloor-nearly-three-years-ago-now-they-finally-know-what-it-is-180988624/</guid></item><item><title>一名 13 岁男孩在田野里发现了这枚铜币。结果是在柏林发现的第一件古希腊文物</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-13-year-old-boy-found-this-bronze-coin-in-a-field-it-turned-out-to-be-the-first-ancient-greek-artifact-discovered-in-berlin-180988627/</link><description>该物品于公元前三世纪在特洛伊铸造，可能是作为送给死者的礼物而埋葬的。考古学家不知道它是如何最终出现在现代德国的</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-13-year-old-boy-found-this-bronze-coin-in-a-field-it-turned-out-to-be-the-first-ancient-greek-artifact-discovered-in-berlin-180988627/</guid></item><item><title>一个新的美洲原住民 DNA 大数据库动摇了科学家关于南美洲人类住区的理论</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-new-big-database-of-dna-from-indigenous-americans-shakes-up-scientific-theories-about-human-settlement-of-south-america-180988628/</link><description>基因组数据为之前未知的移民浪潮提供了证据，生活在墨西哥中部和南部的土著群体从大约 1,300 年前开始蔓延到南美洲和加勒比地区</description><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-new-big-database-of-dna-from-indigenous-americans-shakes-up-scientific-theories-about-human-settlement-of-south-america-180988628/</guid></item><item><title>第二次世界大战期间，柏林大火烧毁了数百幅绘画。现在，博物馆将在线发布丢失艺术品的照片档案</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/fires-in-berlin-destroyed-hundreds-of-paintings-during-world-war-ii-now-a-museum-will-publish-photo-archives-of-the-lost-artworks-online-180988621/</link><description>随着鲁本斯和卡拉瓦乔遗失画作的底片被数字化并在线发布，记录 Gemäldegalerie 藏品的积极努力将在一个世纪后得到回报</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 20:25:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/fires-in-berlin-destroyed-hundreds-of-paintings-during-world-war-ii-now-a-museum-will-publish-photo-archives-of-the-lost-artworks-online-180988621/</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明，星际彗星 3I/ATLAS 来自银河系极其寒冷、孤独的区域</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/interstellar-comet-3i-atlas-came-from-an-extremely-cold-lonely-region-of-the-milky-way-galaxy-new-research-suggests-180988625/</link><description>天文学家分析了彗星接近太阳时散发出的蒸气，发现它含有大量“重”水。这暗示它是在一个寒冷的行星系统中长大的，可能在它的母星形成之前</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 19:26:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/interstellar-comet-3i-atlas-came-from-an-extremely-cold-lonely-region-of-the-milky-way-galaxy-new-research-suggests-180988625/</guid></item><item><title>一名游客在试图摸索大理石雕像时损坏了佛罗伦萨的“海王星喷泉”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-tourist-damaged-florences-fountain-of-neptune-while-attempting-to-grope-its-marble-statue-on-a-dare-180988623/</link><description>修复喷泉的马雕塑和饰带将花费近 6,000 美元。被指控的罪犯是最新一位为了应对同侪压力或追求社交媒体影响力而损坏艺术品的游客</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 17:52:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-tourist-damaged-florences-fountain-of-neptune-while-attempting-to-grope-its-marble-statue-on-a-dare-180988623/</guid></item><item><title>这种骨头嘎吱作响的章鱼几乎有一辆半卡车那么大，一亿年前可能以巨型爬行动物为食</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-bone-crunching-octopus-was-nearly-the-size-of-a-semitruck-and-may-have-feasted-on-giant-reptiles-100-million-years-ago-180988616/</link><description>根据对下颌化石的分析，这种巨大的无脊椎动物可能是顶级掠食者。这项工作表明，古代海洋并不像之前认为的那样完全由长有脊柱的生物统治</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 16:04:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-bone-crunching-octopus-was-nearly-the-size-of-a-semitruck-and-may-have-feasted-on-giant-reptiles-100-million-years-ago-180988616/</guid></item><item><title>观赏在马萨诸塞州海岸捕获的五千万分之一的彩色龙虾。它携带两组遗传信息</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-1-in-50-million-split-color-lobster-caught-off-the-coast-of-massachusetts-its-carrying-two-sets-of-genetic-information-180988615/</link><description>这种看起来不寻常的甲壳类动物有两种色调，一条线将其身体分为橙色的一面和棕色的一面。当两个受精的、未产下的龙虾卵接触时就会发生这种情况，导致其中一个吸收另一个</description><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-1-in-50-million-split-color-lobster-caught-off-the-coast-of-massachusetts-its-carrying-two-sets-of-genetic-information-180988615/</guid></item></channel></rss>